cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper develops a theory of decidable inductive invariants for an infinite-state variant of the Applied pi-calculus, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper focuses on automatic verification of stateful cryptographic protocols with unbounded sessions/nonces. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the structure of depth-bounded protocols within the framework of ideal completions for well-structured transition systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with trace properties and downward-closed properties, which are related to formal language and automata theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a method for inferring inductive invariants that can be used as a certificate of correctness for cryptographic protocols.
